flowRoot.flowPara: Waste segregation is a good start to cleaning up our city. However, in the long run, this is not enough. Zero Waste is easy and practical. It eliminates "dustbins" and trash bags. Please follow these rules when disposing of waste in this building.

text.tspan: This is a Zero Waste building.

flowRoot.flowPara: Waste can never be placed in plastic cover/trash bags.
Please educate all tenants, domestic help accordingly.
For assistance please contact building management.

text.tspan: Vegetarian bins are emptied into the compost daily.
Line these bins with biodegradable bags or newspaper.
Non-vegetarian bins will be given to the BBMP.
Any vegetarian (including eggs) kitchen waste or garden
There is one bin for each material: paper, plastic, metal,
and glass. There is a separate bin for e-waste.
Wash, rinse, and dry recycleables before putting them
in the bin. Do not put these materials in any other bin.
Use the bins in washrooms for used tissue, pads/tampons,
sharps, and uncategorized waste like dust and broken
glass. Given to the BBMP in paper with a red "X".
